    "body": "The group of JSON-RPC around filters,  eth_newFilter and  eth_newBlockFilter to create them, and eth_getFilterChanges (sometimes also eth_getFilterLogs) to query them, has been the main way of listening to blockchain events for a long time, so there are many DApps relying on them.\r\nWhile you can work around them missing via (repeatedly) calling eth_getLogs, those that are not relying on Infura (which also has limitations to filters) are often using filters, esp. as \"web3\" and similar libraries make it pretty easy to work with those filters usually - even if sometimes they may not be 100% reliable, but that's dependent on the clients/nodes being used.\r\nTo make it easy for those DApps to use Erigon, it would be great if you could support this family of calls (and I know, it probably needs its own kind of infrastructure around it, which may be quite some work).",
