    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I was testing Erigon with my apps as part of migrating away from Geth when to my surprise I stumbled upon this unimplemented family of calls (everything else up this point worked perfectly).\r\n\r\nAs it was alluded to above, `eth_newBlockFilter` although crude, is a popular way for applications to listen for transactions that are not emitting events either by omission or by design. Not a golang expert but I suspect this feature is not a quick thing to implement. It would be good to see Erigon move towards feature parity with Geth and eventually supersede it.",
